value.name: organic chemistry - What do (2S,3S) and similar notations mean ...
value.snippet: This means the carbon they are attached to is a chiral center. If a molecule has a chiral center, that means the molecule comes in at least two kinds of isomers called stereoisomers. Two isomers have a molecular formula that is the same, but the structures and arrangements of the two molecules are different.
